<article class="fyre-comment-article">
  <div class="fyre-comment-wrapper">
  
  
  
  <div class="fyre-comment-user">
    <a class="fyre-comment-author"><img src="" class=
    "fyre-user-avatar" alt="reasonfire" /></a>

    <div class="fyre-comment-socialsync fyre-comment-from-livefyre"></div>
  </div>
    
  <header class="fyre-comment-head">
    <a class="fyre-comment-username">reasonfire</a> 
    
    
    <span class="fyre-comment-user-rating" style="display: none;">5pts</span>
    <span class="fyre-comment-like" style="float: right;">
      
    </span>
    
  </header>
  
  <section class="fyre-comment-body">
    <div class="fyre-comment">
      <p><p>Whilst most of this journal may be on the shameful side of feasible, there is a lot that could either be credited or also discredited. While I do appreciate the unfortunate aspect of corruption that exists within political bodies, the state and the media may I also procrastinate slightly with the rash notion that within this article the writer is portraying their own version of stereotyping. I do appreciate that the issue of racism in this world could be compared to a pulsing cancerous tumour spreading across the nations. However, within this blog, the writer emits the stereotype that the collaboration of the afore mentioned groups (political bodies, state, media) may lead to untruths being spread across the globe. In the cases of Maria and Madeline, the fact that they are of European background may affirm the reason behind their positioning in the 'media hotlist' as it were but does that give us the right to speculate as to the reason they are either missing or unidentified. As it is, they are children; children who are missing from their natural home. I agree, we do not have the right to choose if a child is returned to it's family based on the ethnicity of that child. However, we do have the opportunity to turn a witch-hunt into a search. I believe we should cease procrastinating about the route by which the child came into the spotlight and turn our speculating minds to more productive endeavours. Perhaps in doing so we may spread the word about more hidden issues in the process, as when you fight fire with fire, they will only spray water to dampen the flames. When you fight fire with water yourself, they congratulate you and ask why you helped.</p></p>
    </div>
    
  </section>

