    <div class="fyre-comment-socialsync fyre-comment-from-livefyre"></div>
  </div>
    
  <header class="fyre-comment-head">
    <a class="fyre-comment-username">NatashaGerson</a> 
    
    
    <span class="fyre-comment-user-rating" style="display: none;">5pts</span>
    <span class="fyre-comment-like" style="float: right;">
      
    </span>
    
  </header>
  
  <section class="fyre-comment-body">
    <div class="fyre-comment">
      <p><p>@David Lynch<span> Actually that 'welfare check' thing we can only take to be true from the very people who also claimed that MAria, 'of North European genotype' (as established by Greek forenisc anthropologists) and whose teeth were supposed to reveal she was 'closer to six than four years old' (dentists) was and 'abducted missing child' who was, (on the ground of home videos) assessed to have been 'trained like a little bear to dance and beg'. All of which has been disproven in the last ten days: She is Roma, she is four and a half, she was not abducted until 16 oct, and the only reports of her begging were from anynomous quotes in tabloid papers and in the speculation of the police and Smile of the Child.   It was not Panagiotis Pardalis that made the statement about Maria's state, it was the very head of the organisation </span><span>Costas Yannopoulos speaking completely out of turn. Anyone can see that what he says was not true from the picture at the police station of Larissa where the couple with Maria was photographed 20 minutes after coming in. She is wearing her own clothes she was wearing at the camp. They are clean. Her tshirt is white. Sitting with her parents (who'se released arrest pictures have incited waves of hatespeech globally, 'animals' 'primitive' 'obviously degenerate' to name a few) she looks relaxed and a little cheeky, it's later, taken away from the only mother she's ever known, that she looks tearstained, inkstained (from fingerprinting) with mussed hair. No wonder! THAT was the only time that she WAS abducted- by the police!  As it happens, Panagiotis Pardalis is since trying to downplay his bosses speculation. 'Never said she was filthy, we meant, dirty, as they are insanitary places, these camps' 'Where only saying what we see in Athens' (not Farsala, a dump surrounded by cottonfields) , we never said she was malnourished (no, 'low weight, estimated from the age they THOUGHT she was, not actually turned out to be) etc. And I wouldn't know any other word than 'concentration camps' for places where men, women and children are locked up and left to rot in dire circumstances, with bare sanition, bare care, bare food and nothing else. 'Open media access"? Can you read? These were humanitary aid workers finally being let in after much procedure. </span></p></p>
    </div>
    
  </section>

