 So the child slave that was used to dance and beg for money on the streets according to this site should be returned to them. 
The Smile of the Child charity told the BBC that medical examinations 
show Maria is in fact either five or six years old and not four as was 
previously reported, after her birth certificate was found to be a 
forgery and she had no school education.
Based on her characteristics the child slave who utters just a few words in Greek and Roma dialect, is believed to be eastern
 or northern European and victum of human trafficking.
 The Smile Of The Child spokesman Panagiotis Pardalis said 
the girl was found in "bad living conditions and in poor hygiene." I don't think that's a quite nice bungalow.
Police have found the woman had two different 
identification documents and other papers suggested the couple had up to
 14 children, but six were registered as having been born within less 
than 10 months. Her little child labour money bringers.
In trafficking they sell and buy the blue eyed blondes as the most valuable commodities because they know that they will bring the most money. They use them as child labour when they are young and sex slaves when they are older but give her back to the Roma or I will scream that you are racist! 

There is no media to the concentration camps. Just people with cameras taking interviews inside the detention centers.
 <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NgonnC2xrFU" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NgonnC2xrFU</a>
Remember these people are in a detention center not in a five star hotel. For visa violations or illegal entry and they are held until a decision is made to grant them a visa or to repatriate them to their country of departure.
And in later news another girl was found in a Roma family in Dublin. 
<a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-24626422" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-24626422</a></p></p>
